President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has issued an order to reduce direct spending budgetary resources for fiscal year 2022 in each non-exempt budget account. This reduction will take place on October 1, 2021, and will be based on calculations provided by the Office of Management and Budget in its report to Congress on May 28, 2021. The order specifies that all sequestrations must be carried out in accordance with the requirements of section 251A of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act and the specifications outlined in the Office of Management and Budget's report.